%N A390223 Numbers k such that for the k-th almost-equilateral Heronian triangle (triangle with consecutive integer sides and integer area), perimeter - inradius is a prime or semiprime.
%C A390223 Numbers k >= 1 such that A001222(3 * A003500(k) - A001353(k)) <= 2.
%F A390223 The perimeter - inradius of the k-th triangle is b(k) = 3 * A003500(k) - A001353(k), which satisfies the recurrence b(k) = 4*b(k-1) - b(k-2).
%e A390223 a(1) = 1 is a term because 3 * A003500(1) - A001353(1) = 3 * 4 - 1 = 11 is prime, corresponding to the triangle of sides 3,4,5 with inradius 1.
%e A390223 a(6) = 7 is a term because 3 * A003500(7) - A001353(7) = 3 * 10084 - 2911 = 27341 = 19 * 1439 is a semiprime, corresponding to the triangle of sides 10083, 10084, 10085 with inradius 2911.
%p A390223 q:= proc(n) option remember; 4*procname(n-1)-procname(n-2) end proc:
%p A390223 q(1):= 11: q(2):= 38:
%p A390223 select(i -> NumberTheory:-Omega(q(i))<=2, [$1..150]);
